        <abstract> 
<p>Is doing a British <hi rend="italic">Flora</hi> [<hi rend="italic">The student’s flora of the British Islands</hi> (1870)], for students, more scientific and more complete than former editions.</p>  
<p>His opinion of Bentham’s [<hi rend="italic">British</hi>] <hi rend="italic">Flora</hi> [1858].</p> 
            <p>On Croll’s extension of glaciers – a huge relief to get rid of simultaneous cooling of the whole globe.</p> 
<p>Watson’s garbling of passage in JDH’s <hi rend="italic">Flora Indica</hi> is unprincipled.</p> 
        </abstract>
